title: Dominant D Leads Lynx to Third Title
text:
Dominant D Leads Lynx to Third Title 
By Zach Schneider Dominant D Leads Lynx to Third Title October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 9:50 PM CDT 
Minneapolis, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The Minnesota Lynx allowed only 12 points in the second and third quarters combined on Wednesday night en route to a 69-52 win over the Indiana Fever in Game 5 of the WNBA Finals, which clinched the team's third championship in five years. 
Sylvia Fowles led the Lynx with 20 points and 11 rebounds in the winning effort, while Rebekah Brunson also had a double-double with 10 points and 14 rebounds. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Maya Moore struggled offensively and got in second half foul trouble, finishing with only five points, but Seimone Augutus was solid throughout and chipped in with 16 points. 
It's the third WNBA championship in the past five seasons for Minnesota (2011, 2013), but the first of those in which the clinching game came at the Target Center. 
Fowles, a midseason acquisition for Minnesota, was named the WNBA Finals MVP.
